## How to read this

- Each box is a **bounded context** — an autonomous module with its own
  ubiquitous language and lifecycle.
- Each edge is **labeled** with: the integration message/event name,
  the integration pattern (SK / OHS / PL / ACL / CF / SW), and a
  volatility emoji indicating how often the edge changes.
- **Edge direction** indicates information flow. Bidirectional edges
  (rare) indicate Shared Kernel or Partnership relationships.

### Pattern abbreviations

| Code | Pattern | Meaning |
|------|---------|---------|
| SK | Shared Kernel | Shared model fragment; high-trust |
| OHS | Open Host Service | Published API for general consumption |
| PL | Published Language | Stable wire format / contract |
| ACL | Anti-Corruption Layer | Translation barrier shielding consumer |
| CF | Conformist | Consumer accepts producer's model as-is |
| SW | Separate Ways | No integration; problem better solved twice |

